 Lara issue will soon be clear, says Kapil
 Former Pakistan captain Inzamam-ul Haq tries a hookah in Hyderabad on Thursday. (PTI)Chandigarh: Indian Cricket League (ICL) executive board chairman Kapil Dev said that the mystery surrounding former West Indies captain Brian Laras participation in the Twenty20 tournament would be cleared up in the next three or four days. There had been rumours that Lara would not play for the ICL and join the BCCI-promoted Indian Premier League (IPL). Just wait for three to four days, everything will be cleared up about Lara But for us, we are expecting him to play for the ICL, said Kapil. When asked whether the players would be allowed to play for other leagues when no ICL matches were on, Kapil said, certainly, they would be allowed to do so. Our main objective is to promote cricket in the country in a big way.  (PTI) 
